I do not have it.

482
00:46:52,937 --> 00:46:57,889
You need the cube to bring me home,
but I've sent it off. I know not where.

483
00:46:58,385 --> 00:47:00,363
You listen well, brother.

484
00:47:01,807 --> 00:47:03,789
I'm listening.

485
00:47:12,207 --> 00:47:15,542
- Do not touch me again.
- Then don't take my stuff.

486
00:47:15,738 --> 00:47:19,368
You have no idea what you're dealing with.

487
00:47:20,031 --> 00:47:21,844
Uh...Shakespeare in the park.

488
00:47:22,043 --> 00:47:25,542
Doth mother know, you weareth her drapes?

489
00:47:25,741 --> 00:47:28,382
This is beyond you, metal man.

490
00:47:28,576 --> 00:47:30,790
Loki will face Asgardian justice.

491
00:47:30,988 --> 00:47:32,499
He gives up the cube and he's all yours.

492
00:47:32,499 --> 00:47:34,006
Until then,

493
00:47:34,298 --> 00:47:35,884
...stay out of the way.

494
00:47:37,525 --> 00:47:39,504
Tourist.

495
00:47:44,523 --> 00:47:46,504
Okay.

496
00:48:18,521 --> 00:48:20,536
How about that.

497
00:49:23,914 --> 00:49:25,895
That's enough!

498
00:49:28,998 --> 00:49:30,313
Now, I don't know what you plan on doing here.

499
00:49:30,313 --> 00:49:33,185
I've come here to put
and end to Loki's schemes!

500
00:49:33,220 --> 00:49:35,599
Then prove it. Put that hammer down.

501
00:49:35,797 --> 00:49:39,000
Uh...yep! No! Bad call!
He loves his hammer!

502
00:49:40,254 --> 00:49:42,630
You want me to put the hammer down?

503
00:50:09,997 --> 00:50:11,977
Are we done here?

504
00:50:59,355 --> 00:51:04,270
In case it's unclear, you try to escape,

505
00:51:05,951 --> 00:51:11,861
you so much as scratch that glass.

506
00:51:17,915 --> 00:51:22,188
Thirty thousand feet,
straight down in a steel trap.

507
00:51:22,387 --> 00:51:24,725
You get how that works?

508
00:51:26,694 --> 00:51:29,532
Ant.
Boot.

509
00:51:32,538 --> 00:51:34,708
It's an impressive cage.

510
00:51:35,143 --> 00:51:37,946
Not built, I think, for me.

511
00:51:38,147 --> 00:51:40,417
Built for something a lot stronger than you.

512
00:51:40,620 --> 00:51:42,621
Oh, I've heard.

513
00:51:43,657 --> 00:51:48,499
The mindless beast, makes play to be the man.

514
00:51:48,697 --> 00:51:50,717
How desperate are you?

515
00:51:50,717 --> 00:51:54,271
You call on these lost
creatures to defend you.

516
00:51:54,306 --> 00:51:56,779
How desperate am I?

517
00:51:56,978 --> 00:51:58,732
You threaten my world with war.

518
00:51:58,732 --> 00:52:00,945
You steal a force you can't hope to control.

519
00:52:01,184 --> 00:52:04,993
You talk about peace and you kill
cause it's fun.

520
00:52:05,193 --> 00:52:08,232
You have made me very desperate.

521
00:52:08,430 --> 00:52:11,269
You might not be glad that you did.

522
00:52:13,638 --> 00:52:17,280
Ooh. It burns you to come so close.

523
00:52:18,315 --> 00:52:24,157
To have the Tesseract,
to have power, unlimited power.

524
00:52:24,357 --> 00:52:26,361
And for what?

525
00:52:27,931 --> 00:52:31,301
A world for all mankind to share,

526
00:52:31,968 --> 00:52:34,041
and then to be reminded what real power is.
Well let me know if real power...

527
00:52:34,041 --> 00:52:36,325
...will want some magazine or something.

528
00:52:45,446 --> 00:52:50,483
- He really grows on you, doesn't he?
- Loki's gonna drag this out.

529
00:52:50,917 --> 00:52:55,356
- So, Thor, what's his play?
- He has an army called the Chitauri,

530
00:52:55,556 --> 00:52:58,760
that none of Asgard nor any world know.

531
00:52:58,959 --> 00:53:02,831
He means to lead them against your people.
They will win him the earth.

532
00:53:03,032 --> 00:53:06,600
- Return, I suspect, for the Tesseract.
- An army,

533
00:53:06,804 --> 00:53:11,073
- from outer space.
- So he's building another portal.

534
00:53:11,297 --> 00:53:13,928
- That's what he needs Erik Selvig for.
- Selvig?

535
00:53:14,130 --> 00:53:16,358
- He's an astrophysicist.
- He's a friend.

536
00:53:16,563 --> 00:53:19,330
Loki has him under some kind of spell,

537
00:53:19,532 --> 00:53:22,498
- along with one of ours.
- I wanna know why Loki let us take him.

538
00:53:22,703 --> 00:53:25,639
- He's not leading an army from here.
- I don't think we should be focusing on Loki.

539
00:53:25,841 --> 00:53:28,944
That guy's brain is a bag full of cats,
you could smell crazy on him.

540
00:53:29,149 --> 00:53:31,411
I don't care how you speak.

541
00:53:31,610 --> 00:53:35,392
Loki is beyond reason,
but he is of Asgard, and he's my brother.

542
00:53:35,594 --> 00:53:38,125
He killed eighty people in two days.

543
00:53:38,327 --> 00:53:41,803
- He's adopted.
- I think its about the mechanics.

544
00:53:42,008 --> 00:53:46,123
- Iridium, what did they need the Iridium for?
- It's a stabilizing agent.

545
00:53:50,409 --> 00:53:54,423
Means the portal won't collapse
on itself, like it did at SHIELD.

546
00:53:54,626 --> 00:53:57,832
No hard feelings Point Break,
you've got a mean swing.

547
00:53:58,036 --> 00:54:03,467
Also, it means the portal can open as wide,
and stay open as long, as Loki wants.

548
00:54:07,385 --> 00:54:09,643
That man is playing gallaga.

549
00:54:09,913 --> 00:54:13,964
Thought we wouldn't notice, but we did.

550
00:54:15,281 --> 00:54:18,014
- How does Fury even see these?
- He turns.

551
00:54:18,216 --> 00:54:20,240
Sounds exhausting.

552
00:54:20,846 --> 00:54:25,100
The rest of the raw materials, Agent Barton
can get his hands on pretty easily.

553
00:54:25,303 --> 00:54:28,307
Only major component he
still needs is a power source.

554
00:54:28,441 --> 00:54:33,942
A high energy density,
something to kick start the cube.

555
00:54:34,142 --> 00:54:37,181
When did you become an expert in
thermonuclear astrophysics?

556
00:54:37,383 --> 00:54:40,387
Last night.
The packet, Selvig's notes,

557
00:54:40,587 --> 00:54:43,356
the Extraction Theory papers.
Am I the only one who did the reading?

558
00:54:43,559 --> 00:54:46,324
Does Loki need any particular
kind of power source?

559
00:54:46,530 --> 00:54:48,570
He got to heat the cube to a hundred
and twenty million Kelvin

560
00:54:48,570 --> 00:54:50,339
just to break through the Coulomb barrier.

561
00:54:50,339 --> 00:54:54,208
Unless, Selvig has figured out how to
stabilize the quantum tunnelling effect.

562
00:54:54,075 --> 00:54:58,104
Well, if he could do that he could achieve
Heavy Ion Fusion at any reactor on the planet.

563
00:54:57,552 --> 00:54:59,916
Finally, someone who speaks English.

564
00:54:59,940 --> 00:55:04,219
- Is that what just happened?
- It's good to meet you, Dr. Banner.

565
00:55:04,423 --> 00:55:07,430
You're work on anti-electron
collisions is unparalleled.

566
00:55:07,630 --> 00:55:10,630
And I'm a huge fan of the way you lose control

567
00:55:10,630 --> 00:55:12,686
and turn into an enormous green rage monster.

568
00:55:13,353 --> 00:55:16,965
- Thanks.
- Dr. Banner is only here to track the cube.

569
00:55:17,166 --> 00:55:19,773
- I was hoping you might join him.
- Let's start with that stick of his

570
00:55:20,974 --> 00:55:23,661
It may be magical, but it works an
awful lot like a Hydra weapon.

571
00:55:23,668 --> 00:55:26,456
I don't know about that,
but it is powered by the cube.

572
00:55:26,490 --> 00:55:28,968
And I'd like to know how Loki used it to turn

573
00:55:28,968 --> 00:55:32,577
two of the sharpest men I know
into his personal flying monkeys.

574
00:55:32,611 --> 00:55:35,262
- Monkeys? I do not understand.
- I do.

575
00:55:37,538 --> 00:55:40,047
I understood that reference.

576
00:55:40,247 --> 00:55:43,427
- Shall we play it, Doctor?
- This way, Sir.

577
00:55:56,472 --> 00:55:59,674
The gamma readings are definitely consistent

578
00:55:59,674 --> 00:56:02,428
with Selvig's reports on the Tesseract.

579
00:56:01,577 --> 00:56:05,601
- But it's gonna take weeks to process.
- If we bypass their mainframe

580
00:56:05,460 --> 00:56:09,879
and direct a reroute to the Homer cluster,
we can clock this around six hundred teraflops.

581
00:56:11,479 --> 00:56:13,018
All I packed was a tooth brush.

582
00:56:13,372 --> 00:56:15,947
You know, you should come
by Stark Towers sometime.

583
00:56:15,947 --> 00:56:18,465
Top ten floors, all R and D.

584
00:56:18,500 --> 00:56:22,676
- You'd love it, it's candy land.
- Thanks, but the last time I was in New York, I...

585
00:56:22,711 --> 00:56:25,161
kind of broke Harlem.

586
00:56:25,477 --> 00:56:28,874
Well, I promise a stress
free environment. No tension.

587
00:56:28,910 --> 00:56:30,169
No surprises.

588
00:56:30,730 --> 00:56:33,958
- Nothing?
- Are you nuts?

589
00:56:33,994 --> 00:56:36,805
You really have got a lid on it,
haven't you? What's your secret?

590
00:56:36,841 --> 00:56:39,412
Mellow jazz? Bongo drums? Huge bag of weed?

591
00:56:39,412 --> 00:56:40,716
Is everything a joke to you?

592
00:56:40,752 --> 00:56:44,755
Threatening the safety of everyone
on this ship isn't funny.

593
00:56:44,791 --> 00:56:46,581
No offense, Doctor.

594
00:56:46,581 --> 00:56:49,090
No, it....it's alright. I wouldn't
have come aboard if I couldn't

595
00:56:49,126 --> 00:56:53,331
- handle pointy things.
- You're tiptoeing, big man.

596
00:56:53,368 --> 00:56:54,636
You need to strut.

597
00:56:54,348 --> 00:56:56,735
And you need to focus on
the problem, Mr. Stark.

598
00:56:56,420 --> 00:56:59,894
You think I'm not?
Why did Fury call us and why now?

599
00:56:59,850 --> 00:57:02,472
Why not before? What isn't he telling us.

600
00:57:02,696 --> 00:57:05,319
I can't do the equation unless
I have all the variables.

601
00:57:05,768 --> 00:57:07,898
- You think Fury's hiding something?
- He is a spy.

602
00:57:08,451 --> 00:57:11,904
He's a spy. Captain, he's the spy.
His secrets have secrets.

603
00:57:12,499 --> 00:57:13,921
It's bugging him too, isn't it?

604
00:57:14,514 --> 00:57:19,664
- Uh, I just wanna finish my work here and...
- Doctor?

605
00:57:25,470 --> 00:57:30,853
A world like for all mankind,
Loki's jab at Fury about the cube.

606
00:57:30,892 --> 00:57:33,571
- I heard it.
- Well, I think that was meant for you.

607
00:57:33,608 --> 00:57:38,405
Even if Barton didn't post
that all over the news.

608
00:57:38,441 --> 00:57:43,757
The Stark Tower? That big ugly......,
building in New York?

609
00:57:43,793 --> 00:57:47,587
It's powered by Stark Reactors,
self sustaining energy source.

610
00:57:47,624 --> 00:57:50,642
That building will run itself
for what, a year?

611
00:57:50,960 --> 00:57:52,455
That's just the prototype.

612
00:57:52,491 --> 00:57:55,298
I'm kind of the only name in
clean energy right now.

613
00:57:55,334 --> 00:58:00,165
So why didn't SHIELD bring him in
on the Tesseract project?

614
00:58:01,843 --> 00:58:05,112
I should probably look into that once
my decryption programme

615
00:58:05,112 --> 00:58:07,546
finishes breaking into all of SHIELD's secure files.

616
00:58:07,581 --> 00:58:10,246
- I'm sorry, did you say.....?
- Jarvis has been running it since I hit the bridge.

617
00:58:10,444 --> 00:58:13,379
In a few hours we'll know every dirty
secret SHIELD has ever tried to hide.

618
00:58:13,579 --> 00:58:16,311
- Blueberry? - Yet you're confused about
why they didn't want you around?

619
00:58:16,512 --> 00:58:19,961
An intelligence organization that fears intelligence?

620
00:58:19,961 --> 00:58:21,741
Historically not possible.

621
00:58:21,776 --> 00:58:23,449
I think Loki's trying to wind us up.

622
00:58:23,648 --> 00:58:27,880
This is a man who means to start a war,
and if don't stay focused, he'll succeed.

623
00:58:28,081 --> 00:58:30,783
We have orders, we should follow them.

624
00:58:30,983 --> 00:58:33,582
Following is not really my style.

625
00:58:34,249 --> 00:58:36,615
And you're all about style, aren't you?

626
00:58:36,815 --> 00:58:40,917
Of the people in this room, which one is;
a-wearing a spangly outfit, and b- not of use?

627
00:58:41,118 --> 00:58:46,185
Steve, tell me none of this smells
a little funky to you?

628
00:58:48,385 --> 00:58:50,584
Just find the cube.

629
00:59:01,988 --> 00:59:04,220
That's the guy my dad never shut up about?

630
00:59:04,421 --> 00:59:07,353
Wondering if they shouldn't have kept him on ice.

631
00:59:07,987 --> 00:59:11,556
The guy's not wrong about Loki,
he does have the jump on us.

632
00:59:11,757 --> 00:59:14,622
What he's got is an acme dynamite kit.

633
00:59:14,823 --> 00:59:18,887
It's gonna blow up in his face,
and I'm gonna be there when it does..

634
00:59:19,589 --> 00:59:22,156
And I'll read all about it.

635
00:59:23,356 --> 00:59:25,987
Or you'll be suiting up like the rest of us.

636
00:59:26,191 --> 00:59:29,722
Ah, see. I don't get a suit of armor.

637
00:59:29,925 --> 00:59:33,293
I'm exposed, like a nerve.

638
00:59:33,491 --> 00:59:37,256
- It's a nightmare.
- You know, I've got a cluster of shrapnel,

639
00:59:37,461 --> 00:59:40,194
trying every second to crawl its way into my heart.

640
00:59:40,393 --> 00:59:43,928
This stops it. This little circle of light.

641
00:59:44,128 --> 00:59:47,727
It's part of me now, not just armor.

642
00:59:48,324 --> 00:59:52,595
- It's a terrible privilege.
- But you can control it.

643
00:59:52,794 --> 00:59:55,829
- Because I learned how.
- It's different.

644
00:59:56,262 --> 01:00:01,861
Hey, I've read all about your accident.
That much gammer exposure should have killed you.

645
01:00:02,062 --> 01:00:05,196
So you're saying that the Hulk,

646
01:00:05,861 --> 01:00:08,529
the other guy, saved my life?

647
01:00:08,730 --> 01:00:12,029
That's nice.
It's a nice sentiment.

648
01:00:12,230 --> 01:00:14,998
Save it for what?

649
01:00:15,733 --> 01:00:17,896
I guess we'll find out.

650
01:00:19,399 --> 01:00:23,165
- You may not enjoy that.
- You just might.

651
01:01:22,174 --> 01:01:25,307
As soon as Loki took the doctor we moved Jane Foster.

652
01:01:25,507 --> 01:01:28,768
We've got an excellent observatory in Traunsee.

653
01:01:28,768 --> 01:01:31,831
She was asked to consult there
very suddenly yesterday.

654
01:01:31,866 --> 01:01:35,775
Handsome fee, private plane, very remote.

655
01:01:36,276 --> 01:01:39,176
- She'll be safe.
- Thank you.

656
01:01:40,610 --> 01:01:43,543
It's no accident Loki taking Erik Selvig.

657
01:01:43,744 --> 01:01:46,211
I dread what he plans for him once he's done.

658
01:01:46,411 --> 01:01:49,778
- Erik is a good man.
- He talks about you a lot.

659
01:01:50,579 --> 01:01:53,178
You changed his life.

660
01:01:54,245 --> 01:01:58,481
- You changed everything around here.
- They were better as they were.

661
01:01:58,979 --> 01:02:01,879
We pretend on Asgard that
we're more advanced, but we.

662
01:02:02,079 --> 01:02:04,712
We come here battling like Bilchsteim.

663
01:02:04,914 --> 01:02:10,548
- Like what?
- Bilchsteim. You know; huge, scaly, big antlers.

664
01:02:10,749 --> 01:02:12,514
- You don't have those?
- I don't think so.

665
01:02:12,717 --> 01:02:15,048
They are repulsive, and

666
01:02:15,982 --> 01:02:19,048
they trample everything in their path.

667
01:02:25,782 --> 01:02:31,516
When I first came to earth, Loki's rage followed me
here and your people paid the price.

668
01:02:31,719 --> 01:02:34,252
And now again,

669
01:02:36,086 --> 01:02:39,225
n my youth I courted war.

670
01:02:40,351 --> 01:02:42,884
War hasn't started yet.

671
01:02:43,587 --> 01:02:46,487
You think you can make Loki tell us what the Tesseract is?

672
01:02:46,686 --> 01:02:49,920
I do not know. Loki's mind is far afield,

673
01:02:50,118 --> 01:02:54,520
it's not just power he craves,
it's vengeance upon me.

674
01:02:54,954 --> 01:02:57,887
There's no pain that would prise his need from him.

675
01:02:58,086 --> 01:03:02,923
A lot of guys think that, until the pain stops.

676
01:03:04,289 --> 01:03:09,290
- What are you asking me to do?
- I'm asking, what are you prepared to do?

677
01:03:09,491 --> 01:03:10,624
Loki is a prisoner.

678
01:03:10,755 --> 01:03:15,324
Then why do I feel like he's the only person on
this boat that wants to be here?

679
01:03:27,293 --> 01:03:30,293
There's not many people that can sneak up on me.

680
01:03:30,495 --> 01:03:35,092
But you figured I'd come after.

681
01:03:35,293 --> 01:03:38,461
After whatever tortures Fury can concoct,

682
01:03:38,660 --> 01:03:42,495
you would appear as a friend,
as a balm.

683
01:03:43,463 --> 01:03:47,328
- And I would cooperate.
- I wanna know what you've done to Agent Barton.

684
01:03:47,495 --> 01:03:50,596
I'd say I've expanded his mind.

685
01:03:51,993 --> 01:03:56,999
And once you've won. Once you're king of the mountain.

686
01:03:58,064 --> 01:04:01,062
What happens to his mind?

687
01:04:01,896 --> 01:04:07,233
- Is this love, Agent Romanoff?
- Love is for children. I owe him a debt.

688
01:04:10,464 --> 01:04:12,465
Tell me.

689
01:04:16,600 --> 01:04:19,867
Before I worked for SHIELD, I

690
01:04:23,733 --> 01:04:29,235
I made a name for myself.
I have a very specific skillset.

691
01:04:29,437 --> 01:04:33,870
I didn't care who I used it for, or on.

692
01:04:34,068 --> 01:04:37,402
I got on SHIELD's radar in a bad way.

693
01:04:38,672 --> 01:04:41,670
Agent Barton was sent to kill me,

694
01:04:42,669 --> 01:04:44,670
he made a different call.

695
01:04:46,877 --> 01:04:50,208
And what will you do if I vow to spare him?

696
01:04:50,478 --> 01:04:54,508
- I'll not let you out.
- Ah, no. But I like this

697
01:04:54,707 --> 01:04:58,107
Your world in the balance, and you bargain for one man?

698
01:04:58,308 --> 01:05:02,839
Regime's fall everyday.
I tend not to weep over that, I'm Russian,

699
01:05:03,040 --> 01:05:05,141
Or I was.

700
01:05:05,339 --> 01:05:10,269
- And what are you now?
- It's really not that complicated.

701
01:05:10,538 --> 01:05:14,873
I've got red in my ledger, I'd like to wipe it out.

702
01:05:15,636 --> 01:05:17,637
Can you?

703
01:05:18,503 --> 01:05:21,837
Can you wipe out that much red?

704
01:05:23,504 --> 01:05:25,669
Drakoff's daughter?

705
01:05:26,601 --> 01:05:28,602
Sao Paulo?

706
01:05:29,534 --> 01:05:31,534
The hospital file?

707
01:05:32,801 --> 01:05:35,134
Barton told me everything.

708
01:05:35,332 --> 01:05:38,266
Your ledger is dripping, it's gushing red,

709
01:05:38,464 --> 01:05:42,497
and you think saving a man no more virtuous
than yourself will change anything?

710
01:05:42,697 --> 01:05:45,200
This is the basest sentimentality.

711
01:05:45,397 --> 01:05:49,496
This is a child at prayer.
Pathetic.

712
01:05:49,698 --> 01:05:52,429
You lie and kill

713
01:05:52,631 --> 01:05:56,328
